ALGORITHM: INVENTORY MANAGEMENT SYSTEM

Step 1: Start

Step 2: Declare a structure "Item" with fields:
        - Item ID (integer)
        - Item Name (string)
        - Quantity (integer)
        - Price (float)

Step 3: Initialize variables:
        - Create array/vector to store items
        - Set count = 0
        - Declare choice variable

Step 4: Begin loop (repeat until user selects Exit)

Step 5: Display the menu:
        1. Add Item
        2. Display All Items
        3. Search Item
        4. Update Item
        5. Delete Item
        6. Exit

Step 6: Enter user choice

Step 7: Check choice using switch-case or if-else

        Case 1: Add Item
            a. Enter Item ID
            b. Enter Item Name
            c. Enter Quantity
            d. Enter Price
            e. Store item in array at position count
            f. Increment count by 1
            g. Display "Item Added Successfully"

        Case 2: Display All Items
            a. If count == 0
                   Display "Inventory is Empty"
            b. Else
                   For i = 0 to count - 1
                       Display item details

        Case 3: Search Item
            a. Enter Item ID to search
            b. Set found = false
            c. For i = 0 to count - 1
                   If item ID matches
                       Display item details
                       Set found = true
                       Break loop
            d. If found == false
                   Display "Item Not Found"

        Case 4: Update Item
            a. Enter Item ID
            b. Set found = false
            c. For i = 0 to count - 1
                   If item ID matches
                       Enter new Quantity
                       Enter new Price
                       Update values
                       Display "Item Updated"
                       Set found = true
                       Break loop
            d. If found == false
                   Display "Item Not Found"

        Case 5: Delete Item
            a. Enter Item ID
            b. Set found = false
            c. For i = 0 to count - 1
                   If item ID matches
                       For j = i to count - 2
                           Shift items left (arr[j] = arr[j+1])
                       Decrement count by 1
                       Display "Item Deleted"
                       Set found = true
                       Break loop
            d. If found == false
                   Display
